{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859976318,"sessionID":"ses_2867ff157ffeB5aPzhffDhlWLU","part":{"id":"prt_d79805949001LoWNrc4Q11cdoY","messageID":"msg_d7980382d001DELEJ1ItkmGhFx","sessionID":"ses_2867ff157ffeB5aPzhffDhlWLU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_31a0e3b60a0d4fdfb729be29","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Proposal: CLI `pack` Command — AR-020\n\n## Feature Overview\n\n| Attribute | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| **AR ID** | AR-020 |\n| **Module** | cmd/cli |\n| **Command** | `kubectl-agentcube pack` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M |\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) that validates and prepares a workspace directory for agent deployment by:\n\n1. Validating workspace structure (Python/Java requirements)\n2. Loading or creating agent metadata\n3. Applying CLI option overrides\n4. Validating language compatibility\n5. Processing dependencies\n6. Generating Dockerfile (when needed)\n7. Persisting metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n## Motivation\n\nThe `pack` command is the first step in the agent lifecycle management workflow. Before an agent can be built, published, or invoked, it must be validated and packaged with its configuration. This command provides:\n\n- **Validation**: Ensures workspace meets requirements before build/publish\n- **Configuration**: Allows CLI overrides for agent metadata\n- **Preparation**: Generates necessary artifacts (Dockerfile) and metadata files\n\n## Design\n\n### Command Interface\n\n```python\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### Implementation Components\n\n#### 1. Typer Command Binding (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n\n- Add `pack` command to the Typer app\n- Use `@app.command()` decorator\n- Call `PackRuntime.pack()` with resolved options\n- Handle success/failure with Rich output\n\n#### 2. PackRuntime Class (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None\n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]\n    def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata\n    def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata\n    def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None\n    def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None\n    def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]\n    def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str\n    def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str\n    def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None\n    def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path\n    def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str\n```\n\n#### 3. Metadata Models\n\n- **AgentMetadata** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`): Pydantic model for agent configuration\n- **MetadataOptions** (`agentcube/models/pack_models.py`): Dataclass for CLI option overrides\n\n### Workflow\n\n```\n1. Parse CLI arguments\n2. Resolve workspace path\n3. _validate_workspace_structure()\n   - Check directory exists\n   - For Python: require *.py files\n   - For Java: require pom.xml\n4. _load_or_create_metadata()\n   - Load existing agent_metadata.yaml (fallback: agent.yaml, metadata.yaml)\n   - Create new if not exists\n5. _apply_option_overrides()\n   - CLI options override metadata fields\n6. _validate_language_compatibility()\n   - _validate_python_compatibility() / _validate_java_compatibility()\n7. _process_dependencies()\n   - Process requirements.txt / pom.xml\n8. _generate_dockerfile() (if not exists)\n   - Use language-specific template\n9. _update_pack_metadata()\n   - Save to agent_metadata.yaml\n10. Return success with agent_name, workspace_path, metadata_path\n```\n\n### Output Format\n\nOn success:\n```\n✓ Agent 'my-agent' packaged successfully\n  Workspace: /path/to/workspace\n  Metadata: /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml\n```\n\nOn failure (with verbose):\n```\n✗ Error packaging agent: <error message>\n<traceback>\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML serialization |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich terminal output |\n| `packaging>=23.0` | Version handling |\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| AC-001 | Valid Python workspace with existing metadata | Pack succeeds, metadata updated |\n| AC-002 | Valid workspace, no metadata | New metadata created |\n| AC-003 | Nonexistent workspace path | ValueError raised |\n| AC-004 | Python workspace without *.py files | ValueError raised |\n| AC-005 | Java workspace without pom.xml | ValueError raised |\n| AC-006 | CLI option overrides | Metadata fields updated |\n| AC-007 | Workspace without Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated |\n| AC-008 | Invalid language value | Pydantic validation error |\n| AC-009 | Invalid port range | Pydantic validation error |\n| AC-010 | Pack failure | Error message + exit code 1 |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n1. **Single monolithic function**: Could implement all logic in CLI main file, but violates separation of concerns and makes testing harder.\n\n2. **Reuse existing MetadataService**: While MetadataService handles load/save, PackRuntime orchestrates the full pack workflow including validation and generation.\n\n3. **Interactive prompts**: Could prompt for missing required fields, but spec specifies CLI-first approach with error messages.\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Scope\n- New file: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n- Modified: `agentcube/cli/main.py` (add command)\n- New file: `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` (if MetadataOptions not already present)\n\n### Testing\n- Unit tests for PackRuntime methods\n- Integration tests with sample workspaces\n- CLI argument parsing tests\n\n### Documentation\n- Command help text via Typer\n- Optional: CLI user guide\n\n## Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n| Dockerfile generation edge cases | Medium | Medium | Comprehensive template testing |\n| Workspace validation edge cases | Low | Medium | Thorough validation coverage |\n| Metadata override edge cases | Low | Low | Clear Pydantic validation |\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| Implementation | 3-4 hours |\n| Unit tests | 2 hours |\n| Integration testing | 1 hour |\n| **Total** | **6-7 hours** |","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775859976309,"end":1775859976315}}}}
