{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860034883,"sessionID":"ses_2867ff157ffeB5aPzhffDhlWLU","part":{"id":"prt_d7980ec60001wDCKvcFtalN6cc","messageID":"msg_d7980e2180016dKFmEpJY6uG8w","sessionID":"ses_2867ff157ffeB5aPzhffDhlWLU","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_121ffeb6a05b42829f631396","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","newString":"# Proposal: AR-020 — CLI `pack` Command\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) that validates and prepares a workspace directory for agent deployment by validating workspace structure, loading/creating metadata, applying CLI overrides, processing dependencies, generating Dockerfiles, and persisting configuration.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides commands for the complete agent lifecycle: pack, build, publish, invoke, and status. The `pack` command is the first step, preparing the workspace before build/publish.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement the `pack` command that:\n1. Validates workspace structure (Python/Java requirements)\n2. Loads or creates agent metadata\n3. Applies CLI option overrides\n4. Validates language compatibility\n5. Processes dependencies\n6. Generates Dockerfile when needed\n7. Persists metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n### Value\n\n- **Validation**: Ensures workspace meets requirements before build/publish\n- **Configuration**: Allows CLI overrides for agent metadata  \n- **Preparation**: Generates necessary artifacts (Dockerfile) and metadata files\n- **Consistency**: Follows existing CLI patterns and design specs\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| Pack command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command binding |\n| Pack runtime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core pack logic |\n| Metadata models | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | MetadataOptions dataclass |\n| Metadata service | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | AgentMetadata model (existing) |\n\n### CLI Interface\n\n```python\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### PackRuntime API\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None\n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]\n    def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata\n    def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata\n    def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None\n    def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None\n    def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]\n    def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None\n    def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path\n    def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str\n```\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Build command implementation\n- Publish/invoke/status commands\n- Kubernetes deployment logic\n- Interactive prompts (CLI-first approach)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML serialization |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich terminal output |\n| `packaging>=23.0` | Version handling |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- **cli-toolkit/design.md** — Package layout and module structure\n- **cli-toolkit/spec.md** — Pack command requirements and scenarios\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Build command** — Depends on packed workspace with metadata\n2. **Publish command** — Uses metadata for deployment\n3. **End users** — First CLI command in agent workflow\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Dockerfile generation edge cases | Medium | Comprehensive template testing |\n| Workspace validation edge cases | Low | Thorough validation coverage |\n| Metadata override edge cases | Low | Clear Pydantic validation |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Single Monolithic Function (Not Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Implement all logic in CLI main file.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simpler initial implementation\n- Direct function calls\n\n**Cons**:\n- Violates separation of concerns\n- Harder to test\n- Duplicated logic with other runtimes\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — violates project architecture patterns.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: PackRuntime Class (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Dedicated PackRuntime class following existing patterns.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Consistent with BuildRuntime, PublishRuntime patterns\n- Clean separation of concerns\n- Testable unit components\n- Reusable across CLI and other entry points\n\n**Cons**:\n- More initial code\n\n**Decision**: Selected — aligns with existing architecture and design specs.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Interactive Prompts (Not Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Prompt for missing required fields interactively.\n\n**Pros**:\n- More user-friendly for new users\n- Guides through configuration\n\n**Cons**:\n- Complex CLI implementation\n- Spec specifies CLI-first approach\n- Not suitable for CI/CD pipelines\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — spec requires CLI-first approach with error messages.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core PackRuntime\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n- [ ] Implement workspace validation\n- [ ] Implement metadata loading/creation\n- [ ] Implement option overrides\n\n### Phase 2: Dockerfile Generation\n- [ ] Implement Python Dockerfile template\n- [ ] Implement Java Dockerfile template\n- [ ] Implement entrypoint inference\n\n### Phase 3: CLI Integration\n- [ ] Add pack command to main.py Typer app\n- [ ] Implement Rich output formatting\n- [ ] Implement error handling with `_handle_error`\n\n### Phase 4: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for PackRuntime methods\n- [ ] Integration tests with sample workspaces\n- [ ] CLI argument parsing tests\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| AC-001 | Valid Python workspace with existing metadata | Pack succeeds, metadata updated |\n| AC-002 | Valid workspace, no metadata | New metadata created |\n| AC-003 | Nonexistent workspace path | ValueError raised |\n| AC-004 | Python workspace without *.py files | ValueError raised |\n| AC-005 | Java workspace without pom.xml | ValueError raised |\n| AC-006 | CLI option overrides | Metadata fields updated |\n| AC-007 | Workspace without Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated |\n| AC-008 | Invalid language value | Pydantic validation error |\n| AC-009 | Invalid port range (1-65535) | Pydantic validation error |\n| AC-010 | Pack failure | Error message + exit code 1 |\n| AC-011 | Successful pack output | Success message with agent_name, paths |\n| AC-012 | Verbose mode | Detailed logging enabled |\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| Core PackRuntime | 2-3 hours |\n| Dockerfile Generation | 1-2 hours |\n| CLI Integration | 1 hour |\n| Testing | 2 hours |\n| **Total** | **6-8 hours** |","oldString":"# Proposal: AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement 4 CLI binary entry points in the `cmd` module for the agentcube project: `agentd`, `picod`, `router`, and `workloadmanager`. Each binary serves as a distinct service entry point with its own package structure, configuration, and lifecycle management.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe agentcube project comprises multiple independent services that need to be deployed and run as separate processes in a Kubernetes cluster. Currently, only `agentd` and `picod` have binary entry points. The `router` and `workloadmanager` packages exist but lack standalone binary entry points.\n\n### Goal\n\nCreate consistent CLI binary entry points for all 4 core services:\n- **agentd** — Kubernetes controller for idle Sandbox cleanup\n- **picod** — PicoD execution server\n- **router** — HTTP routing, proxy, and session management service\n- **workloadmanager** — Workload orchestration and lifecycle management\n\n### Value\n\n- Consistent CLI interface across all services\n- Standardized flag parsing and configuration\n- Proper signal handling and graceful shutdown\n- Independent deployment and scaling of each service\n- Clear separation of concerns\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Binary | Package | Description |\n|--------|---------|-------------|\n| `agentd` | `cmd/agentd` | Kubernetes controller for idle Sandbox cleanup (existing) |\n| `picod` | `cmd/picod` | PicoD execution server (existing) |\n| `router` | `cmd/router` | HTTP router, proxy, and session management |\n| `workloadmanager` | `cmd/workloadmanager` | Workload orchestration service |\n\n### Code Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── agentd/\n│   └── main.go                  # Binary entry point (existing)\n├── picod/\n│   └── main.go                  # Binary entry point (existing)\n├── router/\n│   └── main.go                  # New binary entry point\n└── workloadmanager/\n    └── main.go                  # New binary entry point\n```\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Multi-binary combined binary (single binary with subcommands)\n- Dynamic service discovery\n- Cross-service communication configuration\n- Deployment manifests (Helm charts, YAML)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n|------------|--------|---------|\n| sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime | v0.19.x | Controller framework for agentd |\n| k8s.io/client-go | existing | Kubernetes client integration |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client | internal | Generated client for runtime API |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery | existing | Kubernetes types and utilities |\n| github.com/gin-gonic/gin | existing | HTTP framework for workloadmanager |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | existing | Logging |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- **AR-012 Workload Manager** — Provides workload orchestration logic\n- **AR-018 Agentd** — Provides idle cleanup controller logic\n- **client-go library** — Generated Kubernetes client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Kubernetes Cluster** — All 4 services run as Deployments\n2. **Operators** — Manage individual service deployments\n3. **End Users** — Access services via router or directly\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Inconsistent flag parsing across binaries | Low | Use consistent flag definitions in each main.go |\n| Missing graceful shutdown in new binaries | Medium | Implement signal handling in router and workloadmanager |\n| Client-go version mismatch | Low | Use consistent version across all binaries |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Single Binary with Subcommands (Baseline)\n\n**Approach**: Create one combined binary with subcommands (`agentcube agentd`, `agentcube router`, etc.).\n\n**Pros**:\n- Single binary to deploy\n- Shared configuration\n- Consistent CLI interface\n\n**Cons**:\n- Larger binary size\n- All services must be deployed together\n- Cannot scale services independently\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — requires independent service deployment and scaling.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Separate Binaries (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Each service has its own binary entry point in `cmd/` directory.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Independent deployment and scaling\n- Smaller individual binaries\n- Clear separation of concerns\n- Matches existing project structure\n\n**Cons**:\n- Multiple binaries to manage\n- Some code duplication in flag parsing\n\n**Decision**: Selected — aligns with existing architecture and deployment requirements.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Shared Framework Binary\n\n**Approach**: Create a shared CLI framework that all services use.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Consistent behavior across services\n- Reduced code duplication\n- Centralized configuration\n\n**Cons**:\n- Added complexity\n- Tight coupling between services\n- Over-engineered for 4 binaries\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — introduces unnecessary abstraction layer.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Router Binary\n- [ ] Create `cmd/router/main.go`\n- [ ] Initialize router config from flags\n- [ ] Set up HTTP server with middleware stack\n- [ ] Implement graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n\n### Phase 2: Workload Manager Binary\n- [ ] Create `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n- [ ] Initialize workloadmanager config from flags\n- [ ] Set up Kubernetes client using pkg/client\n- [ ] Implement graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n\n### Phase 3: Verification\n- [ ] Build all 4 binaries successfully\n- [ ] Verify each binary responds to `-h` flag\n- [ ] Verify graceful shutdown works for each\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` succeeds\n- [ ] `go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod` succeeds\n- [ ] `go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router` succeeds\n- [ ] `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager` succeeds\n- [ ] All binaries accept `-h` flag and display usage\n- [ ] All binaries handle SIGTERM/SIGINT for graceful shutdown\n- [ ] Each binary has consistent flag parsing pattern"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md\n@@ -1,185 +1,226 @@\n-# Proposal: AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n+# Proposal: AR-020 — CLI `pack` Command\n \n ## Summary\n \n-Implement 4 CLI binary entry points in the `cmd` module for the agentcube project: `agentd`, `picod`, `router`, and `workloadmanager`. Each binary serves as a distinct service entry point with its own package structure, configuration, and lifecycle management.\n+Implement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) that validates and prepares a workspace directory for agent deployment by validating workspace structure, loading/creating metadata, applying CLI overrides, processing dependencies, generating Dockerfiles, and persisting configuration.\n \n ## Purpose\n \n ### Background\n \n-The agentcube project comprises multiple independent services that need to be deployed and run as separate processes in a Kubernetes cluster. Currently, only `agentd` and `picod` have binary entry points. The `router` and `workloadmanager` packages exist but lack standalone binary entry points.\n+The AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides commands for the complete agent lifecycle: pack, build, publish, invoke, and status. The `pack` command is the first step, preparing the workspace before build/publish.\n \n ### Goal\n \n-Create consistent CLI binary entry points for all 4 core services:\n-- **agentd** — Kubernetes controller for idle Sandbox cleanup\n-- **picod** — PicoD execution server\n-- **router** — HTTP routing, proxy, and session management service\n-- **workloadmanager** — Workload orchestration and lifecycle management\n+Implement the `pack` command that:\n+1. Validates workspace structure (Python/Java requirements)\n+2. Loads or creates agent metadata\n+3. Applies CLI option overrides\n+4. Validates language compatibility\n+5. Processes dependencies\n+6. Generates Dockerfile when needed\n+7. Persists metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n \n ### Value\n \n-- Consistent CLI interface across all services\n-- Standardized flag parsing and configuration\n-- Proper signal handling and graceful shutdown\n-- Independent deployment and scaling of each service\n-- Clear separation of concerns\n+- **Validation**: Ensures workspace meets requirements before build/publish\n+- **Configuration**: Allows CLI overrides for agent metadata  \n+- **Preparation**: Generates necessary artifacts (Dockerfile) and metadata files\n+- **Consistency**: Follows existing CLI patterns and design specs\n \n ---\n \n ## Scope\n \n ### In-Scope\n \n-| Binary | Package | Description |\n-|--------|---------|-------------|\n-| `agentd` | `cmd/agentd` | Kubernetes controller for idle Sandbox cleanup (existing) |\n-| `picod` | `cmd/picod` | PicoD execution server (existing) |\n-| `router` | `cmd/router` | HTTP router, proxy, and session management |\n-| `workloadmanager` | `cmd/workloadmanager` | Workload orchestration service |\n+| Component | Path | Description |\n+|-----------|------|-------------|\n+| Pack command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command binding |\n+| Pack runtime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core pack logic |\n+| Metadata models | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | MetadataOptions dataclass |\n+| Metadata service | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | AgentMetadata model (existing) |\n \n-### Code Structure\n+### CLI Interface\n \n+```python\n+def pack(\n+    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n+    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n+    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n+    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n+    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n+    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n+    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n+    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n+    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n+) -> None:\n ```\n-cmd/\n-├── agentd/\n-│   └── main.go                  # Binary entry point (existing)\n-├── picod/\n-│   └── main.go                  # Binary entry point (existing)\n-├── router/\n-│   └── main.go                  # New binary entry point\n-└── workloadmanager/\n-    └── main.go                  # New binary entry point\n+\n+### PackRuntime API\n+\n+```python\n+class PackRuntime:\n+    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None\n+    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]\n+    def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n+    def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata\n+    def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata\n+    def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None\n+    def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n+    def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n+    def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None\n+    def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]\n+    def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None\n+    def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path\n+    def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str\n ```\n \n ### Out-of-Scope\n \n-- Multi-binary combined binary (single binary with subcommands)\n-- Dynamic service discovery\n-- Cross-service communication configuration\n-- Deployment manifests (Helm charts, YAML)\n+- Build command implementation\n+- Publish/invoke/status commands\n+- Kubernetes deployment logic\n+- Interactive prompts (CLI-first approach)\n \n ---\n \n ## Impact Analysis\n \n ### Dependencies\n \n-| Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n-|------------|--------|---------|\n-| sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime | v0.19.x | Controller framework for agentd |\n-| k8s.io/client-go | existing | Kubernetes client integration |\n-| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client | internal | Generated client for runtime API |\n-| k8s.io/apimachinery | existing | Kubernetes types and utilities |\n-| github.com/gin-gonic/gin | existing | HTTP framework for workloadmanager |\n-| k8s.io/klog/v2 | existing | Logging |\n+| Dependency | Purpose |\n+|------------|---------|\n+| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n+| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation |\n+| `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML serialization |\n+| `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich terminal output |\n+| `packaging>=23.0` | Version handling |\n \n ### Upstream\n \n-- **AR-012 Workload Manager** — Provides workload orchestration logic\n-- **AR-018 Agentd** — Provides idle cleanup controller logic\n-- **client-go library** — Generated Kubernetes client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n+- **cli-toolkit/design.md** — Package layout and module structure\n+- **cli-toolkit/spec.md** — Pack command requirements and scenarios\n \n ### Downstream Consumers\n \n-1. **Kubernetes Cluster** — All 4 services run as Deployments\n-2. **Operators** — Manage individual service deployments\n-3. **End Users** — Access services via router or directly\n+1. **Build command** — Depends on packed workspace with metadata\n+2. **Publish command** — Uses metadata for deployment\n+3. **End users** — First CLI command in agent workflow\n \n ### Risks\n \n | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n |------|----------|------------|\n-| Inconsistent flag parsing across binaries | Low | Use consistent flag definitions in each main.go |\n-| Missing graceful shutdown in new binaries | Medium | Implement signal handling in router and workloadmanager |\n-| Client-go version mismatch | Low | Use consistent version across all binaries |\n+| Dockerfile generation edge cases | Medium | Comprehensive template testing |\n+| Workspace validation edge cases | Low | Thorough validation coverage |\n+| Metadata override edge cases | Low | Clear Pydantic validation |\n \n ---\n \n ## Alternatives Considered\n \n-### Option 1: Single Binary with Subcommands (Baseline)\n+### Option 1: Single Monolithic Function (Not Selected)\n \n-**Approach**: Create one combined binary with subcommands (`agentcube agentd`, `agentcube router`, etc.).\n+**Approach**: Implement all logic in CLI main file.\n \n **Pros**:\n-- Single binary to deploy\n-- Shared configuration\n-- Consistent CLI interface\n+- Simpler initial implementation\n+- Direct function calls\n \n **Cons**:\n-- Larger binary size\n-- All services must be deployed together\n-- Cannot scale services independently\n+- Violates separation of concerns\n+- Harder to test\n+- Duplicated logic with other runtimes\n \n-**Decision**: Not selected — requires independent service deployment and scaling.\n+**Decision**: Not selected — violates project architecture patterns.\n \n ---\n \n-### Option 2: Separate Binaries (Selected)\n+### Option 2: PackRuntime Class (Selected)\n \n-**Approach**: Each service has its own binary entry point in `cmd/` directory.\n+**Approach**: Dedicated PackRuntime class following existing patterns.\n \n **Pros**:\n-- Independent deployment and scaling\n-- Smaller individual binaries\n-- Clear separation of concerns\n-- Matches existing project structure\n+- Consistent with BuildRuntime, PublishRuntime patterns\n+- Clean separation of concerns\n+- Testable unit components\n+- Reusable across CLI and other entry points\n \n **Cons**:\n-- Multiple binaries to manage\n-- Some code duplication in flag parsing\n+- More initial code\n \n-**Decision**: Selected — aligns with existing architecture and deployment requirements.\n+**Decision**: Selected — aligns with existing architecture and design specs.\n \n ---\n \n-### Option 3: Shared Framework Binary\n+### Option 3: Interactive Prompts (Not Selected)\n \n-**Approach**: Create a shared CLI framework that all services use.\n+**Approach**: Prompt for missing required fields interactively.\n \n **Pros**:\n-- Consistent behavior across services\n-- Reduced code duplication\n-- Centralized configuration\n+- More user-friendly for new users\n+- Guides through configuration\n \n **Cons**:\n-- Added complexity\n-- Tight coupling between services\n-- Over-engineered for 4 binaries\n+- Complex CLI implementation\n+- Spec specifies CLI-first approach\n+- Not suitable for CI/CD pipelines\n \n-**Decision**: Not selected — introduces unnecessary abstraction layer.\n+**Decision**: Not selected — spec requires CLI-first approach with error messages.\n \n ---\n \n ## Implementation Plan\n \n-### Phase 1: Router Binary\n-- [ ] Create `cmd/router/main.go`\n-- [ ] Initialize router config from flags\n-- [ ] Set up HTTP server with middleware stack\n-- [ ] Implement graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n+### Phase 1: Core PackRuntime\n+- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n+- [ ] Implement workspace validation\n+- [ ] Implement metadata loading/creation\n+- [ ] Implement option overrides\n \n-### Phase 2: Workload Manager Binary\n-- [ ] Create `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n-- [ ] Initialize workloadmanager config from flags\n-- [ ] Set up Kubernetes client using pkg/client\n-- [ ] Implement graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n+### Phase 2: Dockerfile Generation\n+- [ ] Implement Python Dockerfile template\n+- [ ] Implement Java Dockerfile template\n+- [ ] Implement entrypoint inference\n \n-### Phase 3: Verification\n-- [ ] Build all 4 binaries successfully\n-- [ ] Verify each binary responds to `-h` flag\n-- [ ] Verify graceful shutdown works for each\n+### Phase 3: CLI Integration\n+- [ ] Add pack command to main.py Typer app\n+- [ ] Implement Rich output formatting\n+- [ ] Implement error handling with `_handle_error`\n \n+### Phase 4: Testing\n+- [ ] Unit tests for PackRuntime methods\n+- [ ] Integration tests with sample workspaces\n+- [ ] CLI argument parsing tests\n+\n ---\n \n ## Acceptance Criteria\n \n-- [ ] `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` succeeds\n-- [ ] `go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod` succeeds\n-- [ ] `go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router` succeeds\n-- [ ] `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager` succeeds\n-- [ ] All binaries accept `-h` flag and display usage\n-- [ ] All binaries handle SIGTERM/SIGINT for graceful shutdown\n-- [ ] Each binary has consistent flag parsing pattern\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n+|----|----------|-----------------|\n+| AC-001 | Valid Python workspace with existing metadata | Pack succeeds, metadata updated |\n+| AC-002 | Valid workspace, no metadata | New metadata created |\n+| AC-003 | Nonexistent workspace path | ValueError raised |\n+| AC-004 | Python workspace without *.py files | ValueError raised |\n+| AC-005 | Java workspace without pom.xml | ValueError raised |\n+| AC-006 | CLI option overrides | Metadata fields updated |\n+| AC-007 | Workspace without Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated |\n+| AC-008 | Invalid language value | Pydantic validation error |\n+| AC-009 | Invalid port range (1-65535) | Pydantic validation error |\n+| AC-010 | Pack failure | Error message + exit code 1 |\n+| AC-011 | Successful pack output | Success message with agent_name, paths |\n+| AC-012 | Verbose mode | Detailed logging enabled |\n+\n+---\n+\n+## Timeline Estimate\n+\n+| Phase | Effort |\n+|-------|--------|\n+| Core PackRuntime | 2-3 hours |\n+| Dockerfile Generation | 1-2 hours |\n+| CLI Integration | 1 hour |\n+| Testing | 2 hours |\n+| **Total** | **6-8 hours** |\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","before":"# Proposal: AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement 4 CLI binary entry points in the `cmd` module for the agentcube project: `agentd`, `picod`, `router`, and `workloadmanager`. Each binary serves as a distinct service entry point with its own package structure, configuration, and lifecycle management.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe agentcube project comprises multiple independent services that need to be deployed and run as separate processes in a Kubernetes cluster. Currently, only `agentd` and `picod` have binary entry points. The `router` and `workloadmanager` packages exist but lack standalone binary entry points.\n\n### Goal\n\nCreate consistent CLI binary entry points for all 4 core services:\n- **agentd** — Kubernetes controller for idle Sandbox cleanup\n- **picod** — PicoD execution server\n- **router** — HTTP routing, proxy, and session management service\n- **workloadmanager** — Workload orchestration and lifecycle management\n\n### Value\n\n- Consistent CLI interface across all services\n- Standardized flag parsing and configuration\n- Proper signal handling and graceful shutdown\n- Independent deployment and scaling of each service\n- Clear separation of concerns\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Binary | Package | Description |\n|--------|---------|-------------|\n| `agentd` | `cmd/agentd` | Kubernetes controller for idle Sandbox cleanup (existing) |\n| `picod` | `cmd/picod` | PicoD execution server (existing) |\n| `router` | `cmd/router` | HTTP router, proxy, and session management |\n| `workloadmanager` | `cmd/workloadmanager` | Workload orchestration service |\n\n### Code Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── agentd/\n│   └── main.go                  # Binary entry point (existing)\n├── picod/\n│   └── main.go                  # Binary entry point (existing)\n├── router/\n│   └── main.go                  # New binary entry point\n└── workloadmanager/\n    └── main.go                  # New binary entry point\n```\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Multi-binary combined binary (single binary with subcommands)\n- Dynamic service discovery\n- Cross-service communication configuration\n- Deployment manifests (Helm charts, YAML)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n|------------|--------|---------|\n| sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime | v0.19.x | Controller framework for agentd |\n| k8s.io/client-go | existing | Kubernetes client integration |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client | internal | Generated client for runtime API |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery | existing | Kubernetes types and utilities |\n| github.com/gin-gonic/gin | existing | HTTP framework for workloadmanager |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | existing | Logging |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- **AR-012 Workload Manager** — Provides workload orchestration logic\n- **AR-018 Agentd** — Provides idle cleanup controller logic\n- **client-go library** — Generated Kubernetes client for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Kubernetes Cluster** — All 4 services run as Deployments\n2. **Operators** — Manage individual service deployments\n3. **End Users** — Access services via router or directly\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Inconsistent flag parsing across binaries | Low | Use consistent flag definitions in each main.go |\n| Missing graceful shutdown in new binaries | Medium | Implement signal handling in router and workloadmanager |\n| Client-go version mismatch | Low | Use consistent version across all binaries |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Single Binary with Subcommands (Baseline)\n\n**Approach**: Create one combined binary with subcommands (`agentcube agentd`, `agentcube router`, etc.).\n\n**Pros**:\n- Single binary to deploy\n- Shared configuration\n- Consistent CLI interface\n\n**Cons**:\n- Larger binary size\n- All services must be deployed together\n- Cannot scale services independently\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — requires independent service deployment and scaling.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Separate Binaries (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Each service has its own binary entry point in `cmd/` directory.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Independent deployment and scaling\n- Smaller individual binaries\n- Clear separation of concerns\n- Matches existing project structure\n\n**Cons**:\n- Multiple binaries to manage\n- Some code duplication in flag parsing\n\n**Decision**: Selected — aligns with existing architecture and deployment requirements.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Shared Framework Binary\n\n**Approach**: Create a shared CLI framework that all services use.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Consistent behavior across services\n- Reduced code duplication\n- Centralized configuration\n\n**Cons**:\n- Added complexity\n- Tight coupling between services\n- Over-engineered for 4 binaries\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — introduces unnecessary abstraction layer.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Router Binary\n- [ ] Create `cmd/router/main.go`\n- [ ] Initialize router config from flags\n- [ ] Set up HTTP server with middleware stack\n- [ ] Implement graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n\n### Phase 2: Workload Manager Binary\n- [ ] Create `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n- [ ] Initialize workloadmanager config from flags\n- [ ] Set up Kubernetes client using pkg/client\n- [ ] Implement graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT\n\n### Phase 3: Verification\n- [ ] Build all 4 binaries successfully\n- [ ] Verify each binary responds to `-h` flag\n- [ ] Verify graceful shutdown works for each\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` succeeds\n- [ ] `go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod` succeeds\n- [ ] `go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router` succeeds\n- [ ] `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager` succeeds\n- [ ] All binaries accept `-h` flag and display usage\n- [ ] All binaries handle SIGTERM/SIGINT for graceful shutdown\n- [ ] Each binary has consistent flag parsing pattern","after":"# Proposal: AR-020 — CLI `pack` Command\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the `pack` command for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) that validates and prepares a workspace directory for agent deployment by validating workspace structure, loading/creating metadata, applying CLI overrides, processing dependencies, generating Dockerfiles, and persisting configuration.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) provides commands for the complete agent lifecycle: pack, build, publish, invoke, and status. The `pack` command is the first step, preparing the workspace before build/publish.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement the `pack` command that:\n1. Validates workspace structure (Python/Java requirements)\n2. Loads or creates agent metadata\n3. Applies CLI option overrides\n4. Validates language compatibility\n5. Processes dependencies\n6. Generates Dockerfile when needed\n7. Persists metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n### Value\n\n- **Validation**: Ensures workspace meets requirements before build/publish\n- **Configuration**: Allows CLI overrides for agent metadata  \n- **Preparation**: Generates necessary artifacts (Dockerfile) and metadata files\n- **Consistency**: Follows existing CLI patterns and design specs\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| Pack command | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command binding |\n| Pack runtime | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Core pack logic |\n| Metadata models | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | MetadataOptions dataclass |\n| Metadata service | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | AgentMetadata model (existing) |\n\n### CLI Interface\n\n```python\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\"),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### PackRuntime API\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None\n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]\n    def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata\n    def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata\n    def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None\n    def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None\n    def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None\n    def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]\n    def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None\n    def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path\n    def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str\n```\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Build command implementation\n- Publish/invoke/status commands\n- Kubernetes deployment logic\n- Interactive prompts (CLI-first approach)\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Data validation |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML serialization |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Rich terminal output |\n| `packaging>=23.0` | Version handling |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- **cli-toolkit/design.md** — Package layout and module structure\n- **cli-toolkit/spec.md** — Pack command requirements and scenarios\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Build command** — Depends on packed workspace with metadata\n2. **Publish command** — Uses metadata for deployment\n3. **End users** — First CLI command in agent workflow\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Dockerfile generation edge cases | Medium | Comprehensive template testing |\n| Workspace validation edge cases | Low | Thorough validation coverage |\n| Metadata override edge cases | Low | Clear Pydantic validation |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Single Monolithic Function (Not Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Implement all logic in CLI main file.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simpler initial implementation\n- Direct function calls\n\n**Cons**:\n- Violates separation of concerns\n- Harder to test\n- Duplicated logic with other runtimes\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — violates project architecture patterns.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: PackRuntime Class (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Dedicated PackRuntime class following existing patterns.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Consistent with BuildRuntime, PublishRuntime patterns\n- Clean separation of concerns\n- Testable unit components\n- Reusable across CLI and other entry points\n\n**Cons**:\n- More initial code\n\n**Decision**: Selected — aligns with existing architecture and design specs.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Interactive Prompts (Not Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Prompt for missing required fields interactively.\n\n**Pros**:\n- More user-friendly for new users\n- Guides through configuration\n\n**Cons**:\n- Complex CLI implementation\n- Spec specifies CLI-first approach\n- Not suitable for CI/CD pipelines\n\n**Decision**: Not selected — spec requires CLI-first approach with error messages.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core PackRuntime\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n- [ ] Implement workspace validation\n- [ ] Implement metadata loading/creation\n- [ ] Implement option overrides\n\n### Phase 2: Dockerfile Generation\n- [ ] Implement Python Dockerfile template\n- [ ] Implement Java Dockerfile template\n- [ ] Implement entrypoint inference\n\n### Phase 3: CLI Integration\n- [ ] Add pack command to main.py Typer app\n- [ ] Implement Rich output formatting\n- [ ] Implement error handling with `_handle_error`\n\n### Phase 4: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for PackRuntime methods\n- [ ] Integration tests with sample workspaces\n- [ ] CLI argument parsing tests\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| AC-001 | Valid Python workspace with existing metadata | Pack succeeds, metadata updated |\n| AC-002 | Valid workspace, no metadata | New metadata created |\n| AC-003 | Nonexistent workspace path | ValueError raised |\n| AC-004 | Python workspace without *.py files | ValueError raised |\n| AC-005 | Java workspace without pom.xml | ValueError raised |\n| AC-006 | CLI option overrides | Metadata fields updated |\n| AC-007 | Workspace without Dockerfile | Dockerfile generated |\n| AC-008 | Invalid language value | Pydantic validation error |\n| AC-009 | Invalid port range (1-65535) | Pydantic validation error |\n| AC-010 | Pack failure | Error message + exit code 1 |\n| AC-011 | Successful pack output | Success message with agent_name, paths |\n| AC-012 | Verbose mode | Detailed logging enabled |\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| Core PackRuntime | 2-3 hours |\n| Dockerfile Generation | 1-2 hours |\n| CLI Integration | 1 hour |\n| Testing | 2 hours |\n| **Total** | **6-8 hours** |","additions":139,"deletions":98},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775860034827,"end":1775860034879}}}}
